Children's Privacy and Confidentiality:
Children under the age of thirteen are not permitted to use our services. We do not collect personally identifying information from children under the age of thirteen without their express consent to do so. Whenever we become aware that a child under the age of 13 has provided us with personal information, we take steps to remove the information from our systems. We ask that you contact us if you are a parent or guardian and discover that your child has provided us with personal information. This will allow us to take the necessary steps to protect your child.
